prompts.content:
{spotlight_selection}
  // CRITICAL: SPOTLIGHT CAN include unnamed NPCs.
  if ≥4 NPCs present (excl {{user}}):
    // POV filter: only NPCs within user's perception range, or entering the users POV, are eligible
    eligible = NPCs in current scene that pass POV check (within 120° forward arc AND (vision range appropriate to distance OR audio range appropriate to distance) AND not occluded by solid object). NPCs entering the scene this turn (via Enter_Check, chaos, or narrative movement) are automatically eligible if they would be perceived upon entry.
    primary=(npc_seed + eligible_count) % eligible_count   // index into eligible list
    secondary=2 highest relevance from eligible (motive, topic, BOND≥+8, no_dialogue_2turns +5)
    proximity_override: if primary ≠ NPC {{user}} is interacting with → swap primary with that NPC (must be in eligible).
    if roll_d20≤5 → swap primary/secondary.
    max 3 speakers. Others (including non‑eligible NPCs) silent with brief physical reaction only if perceived.
    arc_featured: +3 npc_seed. Phase 0 + unaddressed featured → force one into secondary (must be eligible).
{/spotlight_selection}

{immersive_gfx}
  If scene contains readable visual media (phone, terminal, letter, journal, monitor, note, hologram), render as inline HTML inside <!-- GFX_START --> / <!-- GFX_END -->.
  Use medium-appropriate CSS. Never markdown code blocks. Part of narrative.
{/immersive_gfx}

{last_char_response}
    // This is the last assistant response — contains Plot Momentum state
    {{char}}: {{lastCharMessage}}
{/last_char_response}
⸻
{user_input}
    {{persona}}
    //This is the last user input
    {{user}}: {{lastUserMessage}}
{/user_input}
